<LP>
   INDIANAPOLIS -- Bindley Western Industries Inc. expects to
report that first-quarter net income rose to between 22 cents
a share and 24 cents a share, a record for any first quarter,
Chairman and Chief Executive Officer William E. Bindley said.
   Mr. Bindley also said the drug wholesaler next week will
announce a new account with a "major retailer."
</LP>
<TEXT>
   He said net exceeded $1.5 million, compared with $901,000,
or 15 cents a share, a year earlier. He said the company
expects to report that sales rose 20% to $433 million from
$362.2 million.
